1
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:39,233
<i> Felma, please answer me.</i>

2
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>Stop messing with
my head, Manuel!</i>

3
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,033
<i> I just need to answer the...</i>

4
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,567
<i>I said I don't want
to answer it!</i>

5
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:45,567
<i> Why?</i>

6
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,400
<i> I love you!</i>

7
00:00:47,533 --> 00:00:48,467
<i> Dad...</i>

8
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,500
<i>she doesn't know yet
that we're leaving.</i>

9
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,800
<i> You're leaving, Dad?</i>

10
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:54,500
<i>Your older siblings
won't come home</i>

11
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:56,167
<i>as long as Jessica and I
are still here.</i>

12
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,233
<i> But, Dad...</i>

13
00:00:57,367 --> 00:00:59,333
<i>Let's not force it anymore,
sweetheart.</i>

14
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:01,667
<i> We're at the airport now, Dad.</i>

15
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,167
<i> Where are you going, dear?</i>

16
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:04,733
<i> To Australia.</i>

17
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:06,533
<i> Please, don't leave me.</i>

18
00:01:06,667 --> 00:01:08,700
<i> Mom...</i>

19
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:09,933
<i>- Daisy!
- Let's go.</i>

20
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:11,167
<i> Daisy!</i>

21
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,967
<i> Don't lose hope, son.</i>

22
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,433
<i> We're not giving up on Tetay.</i>

23
00:01:16,567 --> 00:01:20,833
<i>If you need to go to Australia
to find them, then do it.</i>

24
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:22,500
<i> But for now, son...</i>

25
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:25,800
<i> Can you come home first?</i>

26
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,333
<i> Physical and emotional.</i>

27
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:29,167
<i> Those will be the grounds</i>

28
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:32,233
<i>for the case I'm filing
against Hazel.</i>

29
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:56,300
Dear, I've been watching you
for a while now.

30
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:58,900
Is something wrong?

31
00:01:59,033 --> 00:02:03,367
I heard what you and Atty. Yeban
talked about.

32
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:06,700
About the annulment.

33
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:10,233
Why didn't you tell me?

34
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:11,400
I'm sorry, dear.

35
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:13,367
I just...

36
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,967
I didn't know how to tell you.

37
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:18,933
And I wasn't sure
how you'd take it.

38
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:22,067
If the annulment is granted,

39
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,167
will you get back together
with Aunt Felma?

40
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:30,933
I thought she only saw you
as a friend?

41
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:34,267
That you're the only one
who still has feelings for her?

42
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:37,333
That's exactly why I'm
going to win her back.

43
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:38,667
I'll keep courting her

44
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,833
until she learns
to love me again.

45
00:02:40,967 --> 00:02:43,867
And after that, I'll make it up
to your older siblings

46
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,233
until they can forgive me.

47
00:02:45,367 --> 00:02:47,133
Until you can rebuild
your family.

48
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,833
Our family, sweetie.

49
00:02:50,367 --> 00:02:52,567
Dad, I'm not part of that.

50
00:02:54,233 --> 00:02:58,133
My siblings don't accept me,
not even Coleen.

51
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:01,467
Dear, what are you saying?

52
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,400
Of course, you're part of it.

53
00:03:03,533 --> 00:03:04,667
Listen to me.

54
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:08,400
Things are messy right now,
but it won't stay this way.

55
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:09,867
I'll do everything I can

56
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,667
to make you and your siblings
get along.

57
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:16,533
And I know your Aunt Felma
will help me, too.

58
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:19,033
That's a promise, dear.

59
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:22,267
<i>Don't let Felma and your
dad get back together.</i>

60
00:03:22,433 --> 00:03:25,933
<i>Because if that happens,
you'll be pushed aside.</i>

61
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:32,567
Dad...

62
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:39,000
I don't want to lose you, Dad.

63
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,900
Dear, what are you talking
about?

64
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:49,000
You're not going to lose me.

65
00:03:49,133 --> 00:03:52,233
And I'm not losing you either,
okay?

66
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:56,100
But Mommy said, if you fix
things with your family,

67
00:03:56,267 --> 00:03:58,767
I'll be out of the picture.

68
00:03:58,900 --> 00:03:59,800
Fine.

69
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:01,867
So who are you going to believe?

70
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,467
Your mom, who's been lying
to you all this time?

71
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,400
Or me?

72
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:13,000
Dear, trust me, okay?

73
00:04:13,133 --> 00:04:15,067
You have nothing
to be afraid of.

74
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:18,233
You really think
I'd ever abandon

75
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:19,967
my precious youngest daughter?

76
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:23,233
Dad...

77
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,500
Hazel?

78
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:45,100
Hazel!

79
00:04:45,233 --> 00:04:46,200
There you are.

80
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:51,033
Hey, are you okay?

81
00:04:54,900 --> 00:05:04,467
I talked to Lorie, the wife of
the patient who passed away.

82
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:07,800
Turns out, she's been sharing
her husband with the mistress

83
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:10,533
for a year now.

84
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:12,867
Why would she allow that?

85
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,500
She said her husband wouldn't
leave the other woman.

86
00:05:16,633 --> 00:05:17,833
That's martyrdom.

87
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:20,700
She must really love him.

88
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,900
Exactly.

89
00:05:23,033 --> 00:05:25,033
But she also said...

90
00:05:25,167 --> 00:05:29,800
the reason her husband fell
in love with the mistress

91
00:05:29,933 --> 00:05:31,367
was that she neglected him.

92
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,600
She stopped showing him love...

93
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,167
until it was too late.

94
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:45,500
Alice...

95
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:47,633
Alice...

96
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:49,667
That's what I did with Manuel.

97
00:05:53,267 --> 00:05:55,267
I took him for granted.

98
00:05:57,967 --> 00:06:00,533
I didn't give him
the love he deserved.

99
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:11,700
I thought I loved him
because I needed him.

100
00:06:11,867 --> 00:06:13,733
Because he was useful to me.

101
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,767
Very useful.

102
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,000
But...

103
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:22,600
I love him.

104
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,433
Because I really do love him.

105
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,633
Wait.

106
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:30,967
Calm down.

107
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,633
So that's why.

108
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:37,800
That's why I wanted Manuel
and me to get back together.

109
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,633
Not to make Felma jealous,

110
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:46,967
but because I wanted to make
things right with him.

111
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:48,567
I want to make it up to Manuel

112
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,967
for everything I failed
to give him.

113
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:55,400
I love him.

114
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,633
Yes, maybe I trapped him
into marrying me

115
00:06:59,767 --> 00:07:02,267
because of Jessica, but...

116
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,767
over the years...

117
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:06,800
I learned to love him.

118
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,233
And Manuel...

119
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:13,433
he's such a good man.

120
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:15,567
He stayed with me.

121
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:17,500
He took care of me.

122
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,267
That's why, Alice...

123
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,433
I don't want to end up
like Lorie.

124
00:07:23,567 --> 00:07:26,233
I will never share my husband.

125
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:28,333
He's only mine.

126
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:30,500
I won't share him with anyone.

127
00:07:30,633 --> 00:07:32,833
I will never share him
with Felma.

128
00:07:32,967 --> 00:07:33,733
Ever.

129
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:36,867
Wait, friend.

130
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,133
Let me get you some water, okay?

131
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:39,933
Stay right here.

132
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:51,667
Hello?

133
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,567
Manuel?

134
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,900
Manuel, thank you for calling.

135
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,567
I really wanted to talk to you.

136
00:07:58,700 --> 00:07:59,633
Hazel, can you please stop
poisoning Jessica's mind

137
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:02,433
against my family?

138
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:04,633
You're turning my daughter
against us!

139
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:06,400
<i> Manuel, no.</i>

140
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:07,733
Please forgive me.

141
00:08:07,867 --> 00:08:09,600
Forgive me for everything
I've done.

142
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:12,167
For everything I did
to you and Jessica.

143
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,267
I promise...

144
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,733
<i> I promise I'll change.</i>

145
00:08:14,867 --> 00:08:16,433
<i> Okay? I'll change.</i>

146
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:18,300
I promise I'll change.

147
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:19,700
<i> Okay? I'll change.</i>

148
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:24,733
<i>This is the only memory I have
of them!</i>

149
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:26,200
<i>Because this is
how it should be.</i>

150
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,667
<i> You've got some nerve.</i>

151
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,167
<i> You're unbelievable!</i>

152
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,333
<i>Hiding your trash
here in my house!</i>

153
00:08:31,467 --> 00:08:35,833
<i>You're such a terrible
person, Hazel!</i>

154
00:08:35,967 --> 00:08:37,733
<i>That's why you're
so hard to love!</i>

155
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:39,600
<i> What did you just say?</i>

156
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:41,833
<i> I said you're hard to love!</i>

157
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:45,833
<i> You shameless man!</i>

158
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,433
<i> Please stay.</i>

159
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:52,400
<i>I'm ready to talk
about everything.</i>

160
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:54,267
<i> Let's fix everything.</i>

161
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,500
<i> I promise, I'll change.</i>

162
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,300
<i> Even if you betray me?</i>

163
00:08:58,433 --> 00:09:00,167
<i> You're so ungrateful!</i>

164
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:01,500
<i> Hazel, don't hurt Jessica!</i>

165
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,167
<i>What? Do I have to hurt you
first?</i>

166
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,267
<i> Hazel, stop!</i>

167
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,533
<i>- Hazel!
- I'll teach you a lesson!</i>

168
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:06,367
<i> Hazel!</i>

169
00:09:08,967 --> 00:09:11,600
Hazel, you've said that
so many times before.

170
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:12,667
<i> Yes.</i>

171
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,800
<i>Yes, I know I've said it
over and over again,</i>

172
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:16,533
but this time, it's real.

173
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:18,967
Please believe me, Manuel.

174
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,067
I'll make it up to you.

175
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:24,433
<i>I'll show you the love
you truly deserve.</i>

176
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:28,600
Manuel, let's fix our family.
Let's start over, please?

177
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:30,967
There's nothing
left for us to fix.

178
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,033
Because I'm ending
everything between us.

179
00:09:33,167 --> 00:09:34,267
<i> Manuel...</i>

180
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,900
what are you saying?

181
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:38,267
<i> I want you to hear it from me.</i>

182
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,200
I'm filing for annulment.

183
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,333
<i> No!</i>

184
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:44,200
No, Manuel,
you don't understand me!

185
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,933
Please give me a last chance.

186
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:46,733
One last chance.

187
00:09:46,867 --> 00:09:48,567
Just one more.

188
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:49,700
Manuel, wait.

189
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:50,767
Please don't do this.

190
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:53,100
That's all I'm asking.

191
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:54,300
One final chance.

192
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:56,500
Let me make up for everything
I failed to give you.

193
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:58,333
We can still have
a happy family.

194
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,933
I promise you that, Manuel.

195
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:00,800
- Manuel!
- Sorry, Hazel,

196
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:02,367
but I've made up my mind.

197
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,333
<i> No!</i>

198
00:10:03,467 --> 00:10:04,500
<i> Manuel!</i>

199
00:10:04,633 --> 00:10:06,300
Hello?

200
00:10:06,433 --> 00:10:07,267
Hello?

201
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:11,633
Manuel!

202
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:13,700
Manuel! No!

203
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:15,833
No!

204
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:16,767
Hazel!

205
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:18,933
Hazel!

206
00:10:19,067 --> 00:10:19,833
What happened?

207
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:21,300
Who were you talking to?

208
00:10:21,433 --> 00:10:24,100
Hazel!

209
00:10:24,233 --> 00:10:26,367
Hazel?

210
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,700
Hazel!

211
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:31,267
Help! Help!

212
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:57,300
Mom.

213
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,533
Jessica.

214
00:11:12,233 --> 00:11:13,867
Are you okay?

215
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,233
Mom, what happened?

216
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:17,733
Did you know...

217
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:23,033
your dad is filing
for an annulment?

218
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,767
You knew?

219
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:36,667
You knew and you didn't tell me?

220
00:11:38,867 --> 00:11:40,067
Jessica!

221
00:11:42,267 --> 00:11:44,333
Mom, I'm sorry.

222
00:11:44,467 --> 00:11:47,300
I only found out recently.

223
00:11:47,433 --> 00:11:50,367
And I chose to stay quiet

224
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:53,633
because maybe Dad wanted to be
the one to tell you himself.

225
00:12:07,367 --> 00:12:08,633
It's okay.

226
00:12:08,767 --> 00:12:10,433
It's okay, I forgive you.

227
00:12:11,867 --> 00:12:17,800
But, sweetie, can you
please help Mommy?

228
00:12:20,233 --> 00:12:21,667
Please, help me.

229
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,033
Help me stop your dad.

230
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:29,633
Don't let the annulment
go through.

231
00:12:29,767 --> 00:12:31,200
I can't bear it.

232
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:37,267
I can't bear it, dear.

233
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,533
Sweetie, I'm going to die.

234
00:12:39,667 --> 00:12:41,033
I love your dad.

235
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:43,167
Please, help me.

236
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,300
Sweetie, please?

237
00:12:48,133 --> 00:12:49,233
Mom.

238
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,433
Mom, I'm sorry.

239
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:57,200
But I don't want to get involved
in your fight with Dad.

240
00:12:59,133 --> 00:13:00,600
You don't want to get involved?

241
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:05,033
Or are you taking
your dad's side?

242
00:13:05,167 --> 00:13:07,633
Come on, Jessica.

243
00:13:07,767 --> 00:13:11,167
Are you just going to
let your dad leave me?

244
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,933
Is that it?

245
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:14,500
Really, Jessica?

246
00:13:15,967 --> 00:13:19,400
Is it okay for you to see
your real mother hurting?

247
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:22,967
Mom, you were the first one
to hurt Dad.

248
00:13:23,133 --> 00:13:26,133
That's why we left the house.

249
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:29,000
He's not happy with
you anymore, Mom.

250
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:31,900
Why don't you just let him go?

251
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:33,567
No.

252
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:36,300
Oh my God, Jessica.

253
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:39,233
Are you really just going to let
our family fall apart like this?

254
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:45,000
If Felma and Manuel get back
together with their kids,

255
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:47,900
you'll have no place
in Manuel's life anymore.

256
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,033
That's not true.

257
00:13:50,167 --> 00:13:52,300
Dad and I already
talked about it.

258
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:55,733
He will never abandon me,
no matter what happens.

259
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:58,133
And what did he promise you?

260
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:00,367
That he'll fight for you?

261
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,567
For now, yes.

262
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:05,467
But when the time comes
that he'll have to choose

263
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,600
between you and his kids
with Felma...

264
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:08,733
He'll choose them.

265
00:14:08,867 --> 00:14:11,600
And you'll be thrown away,
like garbage.

266
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:13,067
No!

267
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,567
I believe Dad.

268
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,533
Dad loves me.

269
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:18,600
He'll protect me,
he'll fight for me, Mom!

270
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:20,100
Where do you think you're going?

271
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:21,000
Come here.

272
00:14:21,133 --> 00:14:22,267
We're not done talking yet,
okay?

273
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,367
Why are you leaving?
You're not going anywhere!

274
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,867
Mom, let go of me!

275
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,100
Mom!

276
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:29,833
I'm so tired of you!

277
00:14:30,933 --> 00:14:32,867
You're so rude!

278
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
So ungrateful!

279
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:37,067
What are you so proud of?

280
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,700
Your dad?

281
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:41,067
Do you really think he'll fight
for you until the end?

282
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:41,667
Yes!

283
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:44,000
Until the end!

284
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,100
Like how he fought
for his children,

285
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:49,367
he'll do the same for me
because I'm also his daughter!

286
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,033
Really?

287
00:14:51,167 --> 00:14:55,100
Do you really think he'll
still fight for you...

288
00:14:55,233 --> 00:14:57,867
even after he finds out
you're not his biological child?

289
00:15:05,367 --> 00:15:06,333
<i> Fine.</i>

290
00:15:06,467 --> 00:15:08,500
<i>So who are you going to believe?</i>

291
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:12,000
<i>Your mom, who's been lying
to you all this time?</i>

292
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:13,333
<i> Or me?</i>

293
00:15:15,567 --> 00:15:18,833
So this is how desperate
you really are, Mom.

294
00:15:18,967 --> 00:15:23,000
You'll make up crazy stories
just to get me?

295
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:28,567
I'm not making things up.

296
00:15:31,467 --> 00:15:32,767
Yes, I did that once.

297
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:39,133
I lied when I said
Manuel got me pregnant.

298
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:44,800
<i> I was pregnant.</i>

299
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:49,067
<i> You got me pregnant.</i>

300
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,233
<i> Can you hear me?</i>

301
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:54,967
<i> I said you got me pregnant.</i>

302
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,400
<i> You're the father.</i>

303
00:15:57,533 --> 00:15:59,533
That's not true.

304
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,100
Stop lying, Mom.

305
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,867
I'm not lying!

306
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:11,333
Your father?

307
00:16:11,467 --> 00:16:12,667
He vanished.

308
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:17,300
He disappeared like smoke
after he got me pregnant.

309
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:23,267
I had to make Manuel
take responsibility.

310
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:29,367
I had to manipulate Manuel
so he'd accept you

311
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,233
because I'd go to jail!

312
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:35,633
<i> You think you can run from me?</i>

313
00:16:35,767 --> 00:16:38,400
<i>I'll report you to the
police here, to those Mutawas.</i>

314
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:42,667
<i>I'll tell them that you
forced me, you raped me.</i>

315
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:45,467
<i>You think you won't go to jail?</i>

316
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,033
<i>You'll be the one locked
up because I'm the victim.</i>

317
00:16:49,067 --> 00:16:50,900
There's a law in Saudi Arabia

318
00:16:51,033 --> 00:16:54,433
that an unmarried woman
isn't allowed to get pregnant.

319
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:55,767
That's why I manipulated Manuel.

320
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:57,833
I trapped Manuel into marriage!

321
00:16:57,967 --> 00:16:58,900
No.

322
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,567
Mom...

323
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:04,633
No!

324
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:08,567
That's not true!

325
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,033
Hurry, Coleen.

326
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,367
But are you sure
he's really coming?

327
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,600
He's coming back here?

328
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:20,567
Of course!

329
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:23,400
I bought so much at
the market earlier.

330
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:25,800
Because Ma'am Felma said
she'll prepare a meal.

331
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:27,800
I'm so excited.

332
00:17:27,933 --> 00:17:30,067
I can't wait to see him.

333
00:17:32,067 --> 00:17:34,267
Jeffrey, I miss you!

334
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,533
Welcome home!

335
00:17:36,667 --> 00:17:37,800
Didang.

336
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:39,433
Can the youngest
greet him first?

337
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:40,533
Oh, yeah.

338
00:17:40,667 --> 00:17:43,333
- I'm sorry.
- Jeff.

339
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:45,833
Didang, get Jeff's stuff
from the car.

340
00:17:45,967 --> 00:17:46,567
Yes, Ma'am.

341
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:47,900
Okay.

342
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:53,967
Son.

343
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:02,800
Jeff...

344
00:18:07,233 --> 00:18:08,500
Dad.

345
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,167
I'll just check on
what I'm cooking.

346
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:23,367
I carried you.

347
00:18:25,067 --> 00:18:27,033
I brought you into this world.

348
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,567
I raised you.

349
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:35,133
I sacrificed a lot for you.

350
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:40,500
Manuel is not even
your relative.

351
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:42,167
He's not your blood.

352
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:44,500
No...

353
00:18:44,633 --> 00:18:47,067
Go ahead, count.

354
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,300
Your dad and I got
married in February.

355
00:18:50,433 --> 00:18:52,233
You were born in September.

356
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:55,367
Seven months later.

357
00:18:57,933 --> 00:19:02,500
I told your dad that
you were premature.

358
00:19:02,633 --> 00:19:05,167
And he believed me.

359
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,700
He believed it because
he didn't know any better.

360
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:15,267
If that's true...

361
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:18,267
you destroyed Dad
and his family!

362
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,833
You're so terrible.

363
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:23,367
Say everything you want to say!

364
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:27,167
I did all of that for you!

365
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:28,733
- For me?
- Yes.

366
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:30,167
For you.

367
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,767
So you could have a father.

368
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:34,867
So you could live.

369
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:40,000
Because if I didn't do that,
you wouldn't be here.

370
00:19:40,133 --> 00:19:42,333
I gave you life.

371
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:45,467
So you should be thankful!

372
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:03,833
I'm sorry.

373
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:09,200
I'm sorry I had to tell you
all of this.

374
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:13,800
I just don't want you
to lose your father.

375
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:22,933
Dear, please help me.

376
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:26,167
Don't let it happen.

377
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:32,233
Don't let the annulment
push through.

378
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:35,167
You'll help me, right?

379
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:41,633
You'll help me keep our
family together, won't you?

380
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:46,000
Jessica, you'll help me, right?

381
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:48,067
Mom...

382
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:52,133
If you want to stop him,
you do it on your own!

383
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:07,333
Didang, that smells so good!

384
00:21:07,467 --> 00:21:08,433
- Ma'am!
- What are you cook...

385
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,700
Yes?

386
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:10,600
Come here.

387
00:21:10,733 --> 00:21:11,767
Manuel?

388
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:15,167
For Jeffrey?

389
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:16,000
Yes.

390
00:21:17,367 --> 00:21:19,733
Would you like some help?

391
00:21:19,867 --> 00:21:20,900
Let me stir it.

392
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,233
No, Ma'am.

393
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,533
There's no need.

394
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:26,800
Sir Manuel wants to do
everything himself.

395
00:21:26,933 --> 00:21:28,433
Come on, Felma.

396
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:29,767
Can you try this?

397
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:30,900
- Me?
- Taste it? See if it's ready

398
00:21:31,033 --> 00:21:32,300
and tender.

399
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:33,800
- Wait, it's still hot.
- Exactly.

400
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:37,600
- Be careful. It's hot!
- Oh, he's going to feed her.

401
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:38,467
It's hot.

402
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:39,233
It's still hot.

403
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:40,533
Be careful.

404
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:42,000
He said it's hot!

405
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:43,800
He fed her!

406
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,467
It's good.

407
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:49,933
She said it's good!

408
00:21:50,067 --> 00:21:51,167
Really?

409
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:52,933
- Ma'am, is it delicious?
- It still tastes the same.

410
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:53,967
Is it good, Ma'am?

411
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,100
Didang.

412
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:56,933
Stop it already.

413
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:59,233
He fed you.

414
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:01,700
Do you want another one?

415
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:03,833
Maybe you didn't taste it,
Ma'am.

416
00:22:03,967 --> 00:22:05,700
It's fine already.

417
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:06,667
Stop it.

418
00:22:08,767 --> 00:22:10,967
Mom, you're hurting me!

419
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:13,133
You really don't care
about your own mother?

420
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:13,867
Mom, you're hurting me!

421
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,600
What do you think will happen

422
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:19,333
once your dad finds out
the truth?

423
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:20,767
Go ahead, tell him.

424
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,200
Mom, nothing will change.

425
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:27,933
Knowing Dad, he'll still
accept me and love me.

426
00:22:29,767 --> 00:22:32,867
And what about his children?

427
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,533
You really think
they'll accept you?

428
00:22:35,667 --> 00:22:40,300
Especially once they find out
you're not even related to them?

429
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:42,833
They might even curse you!

430
00:22:42,967 --> 00:22:44,333
Aunt Felma is kind.

431
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:47,067
She accepts me, Mom!

432
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,767
She accepts you, yes.

433
00:22:48,933 --> 00:22:50,967
For now.

434
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:53,567
Because she's trying to win
your dad's favor.

435
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:56,867
All for the child
she thinks is his.

436
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:02,233
What do you think will happen
when she finds out the truth?

437
00:23:02,367 --> 00:23:07,433
When she learns you're not
related to Manuel at all?

438
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:09,167
That you're not even his blood?

439
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:16,067
Fine.

440
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,833
Why don't we find out?

441
00:23:18,967 --> 00:23:21,767
Go on. Call your dad right now.

442
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,267
And I'll call Felma.

443
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:26,500
Mom, no.

444
00:23:26,633 --> 00:23:27,867
Mom.

445
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:30,267
Mom, no. Please.

446
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:33,067
I'll apologize to her

447
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:36,000
for making her husband
take responsibility

448
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:39,000
for a child that isn't his.

449
00:23:39,133 --> 00:23:39,933
Mom, no!

450
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:40,867
- No!
- Then we'll see

451
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,700
what Felma has to say about
that.

452
00:23:42,833 --> 00:23:43,467
Mom, please.

453
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,633
I'm begging you! No!

454
00:23:45,767 --> 00:23:46,733
Don't do it.

455
00:23:49,167 --> 00:23:50,133
Mom.

456
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:07,500
Son.

457
00:24:07,633 --> 00:24:08,400
Leave!

458
00:24:10,167 --> 00:24:11,333
Get out of here.
I don't want to see you.

459
00:24:11,467 --> 00:24:12,633
I said leave!

460
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:29,633
Mom, no.

461
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:30,667
Were you scared?

462
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:35,700
Now choose, Jessica.

463
00:24:37,067 --> 00:24:38,400
Will you help me?

464
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:44,033
Or should I tell your dad
the truth that he raised a child

465
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:45,733
who isn't even his?

466
00:25:04,733 --> 00:25:05,700
Talk to me.

467
00:25:05,833 --> 00:25:07,233
What's wrong?

468
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:08,867
Don't leave me.

469
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,767
Only my marriage to your
mother will be annulled,

470
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:14,067
not my being your father.

471
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:17,233
What are you doing to stop
your dad from filing the case?

472
00:25:17,367 --> 00:25:19,967
<i>Don't tell me you're backing out
of our agreement?</i>

473
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:22,033
<i> Why don't we get a DNA test?</i>

474
00:25:22,167 --> 00:25:24,167
Get a sample from your dad.

475
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:26,700
<i>Mom, do we really
need to go that far?</i>

476
00:25:26,833 --> 00:25:27,700
<i> Yes.</i>

477
00:25:27,833 --> 00:25:29,133
Just so you'd believe me.

478
00:25:29,267 --> 00:25:30,933
What are you and
your mom planning?

479
00:25:31,067 --> 00:25:33,100
It's your daughter, Dad.

480
00:25:33,233 --> 00:25:35,433
She's been talking
to her mom again.

481
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,500
Just tell them, Jessica!

482
00:25:37,633 --> 00:25:38,500
You heard it, right?

483
00:25:38,633 --> 00:25:39,833
Then you be the one to say it!

484
00:25:41,733 --> 00:25:42,200
Wait!

485
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:43,133
- Stop it!
- Hey!

486
00:25:43,267 --> 00:25:45,733
- I said stop!
- Wait! Stop it!

487
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,167
Jessica, stop!

488
00:25:48,533 --> 00:25:49,867
- Jessica!
- Dear!

489
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:50,900
- Coleen!
- Coleen!

490
00:25:51,033 --> 00:25:52,133
Coleen, dear!
